|[img[Fuzzy Sidebar Search Screenshot]] |^This plugin adds fuzzy searches to ~TiddlyWiki's sidebar search: an additional "Fuzzy" search result tab will automatically appear as you enter search terms into the sidebar search box. |

You can make the "Fuzzy" search tab your default result tab. And you can configure whether you want searches to match //all// terms, or just //any// of your search terms.

These are the [[Control Panel settings|$:/core/ui/ControlPanel/Settings]] related to fuzzy searching:

* [[Fuzzy Term Searching|$:/plugins/TheDiveO/TwFusejs/ui/ControlPanel/everyorall]] -- do you want to search for //all// or //any// of your search terms? (defaults to //all//)

* [[Default Search Result List|$:/plugins/TheDiveO/TwFusejs/ui/ControlPanel/fusedefaultsearchresultlist]] -- when you use TiddlyWiki's sidebar search: do you want to see the fuzzy search results list per default, or the standard list?

* [[Extended Search Syntax|$:/plugins/TheDiveO/TwFusejs/ui/ControlPanel/fuseextendedsearch]] -- fine tune your searches using funny symbols; for details, please refer to [[Fuse.js extended search|https://fusejs.io/examples.html#weighted-search]].